# Settings persistence (extension)

- **Source of truth** is [`apps/extension/lib/settings.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/settings.ts): `loadSettings` / `saveSettings`. Do not add parallel `browser.storage` writes for the same fields elsewhere without updating this layer.
- **Sync slice mirror**: preference fields that also go to `browser.storage.sync` are **mirrored under `storage.local`** (`TABOCALYPSE_SETTINGS_LOCAL_KEYS` includes that key) so saves stay reliable when sync is unavailable, over quota, or slow; `loadSettings` merges cloud sync with the local mirror (mirror wins on overlap).
- **Cross-tab**: the new-tab app listens for `browser.storage.onChanged` and reloads when `isTabocalypseSettingsStorageChange` matches — keep that helper accurate if you add new settings keys or storage areas.
- **User expectation**: treat **persisted state** as immediate for normal controls (`persist` → `saveSettings`). Only use debounced disk writes where the payload is large or chatty (e.g. “My lines”), and document why if you add more debounced paths.
